52.7	Elliott_Carter	Elliott Carter	Elliott Cook Carter Jr. (born December 11, 1908) is a two-time Pulitzer Prize-winning American composer born and living in New York City. He studied with Nadia Boulanger in Paris in the 1930s, and then returned to the United States. After a neoclassical phase, he went on to write atonal, rhythmically complex music. His compositions, which have been performed all over the world, include orchestral and chamber music as well as solo instrumental and vocal works.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d2/ElliottCarter_part.jpg/220px-ElliottCarter_part.jpg
